    "body": "The worrying bit in the OP's sample is the `\"./src/js/**/*.js\"` glob. You _can_ still use browserify for multiple entry points, if you have one per page for example. Many modules might be shared between pages, though, so generating a full separate bundle for each can be very inefficient. [factor-bundle](https://www.npmjs.com/package/factor-bundle) was made to solve that problem: you get a small bundle for each different page, and a separate bundle that contains all code that is shared between bundles. Then you include both in the page and get efficient page loads.\r\n\r\nI think factor-bundle is also compatible with watchify, so I'd recommend using watchify during development.",
