    "body": "Only calling it on views makes more sense to me than calling it on every file. However you're still generating many bundles with mostly duplicate code. It'll be faster and smaller by doing _something_ like\r\n\r\n```js\r\nglob('./src/js/views/*.js', function (err, entries) {\r\n  browserify({ entries: entries, debug: true })\r\n     .plugin(require('factor-bundle'), {\r\n       outputs: entries.map(function (name) { return name.replace(/\\.js$/, '.bundle.js') })\r\n     })\r\n     .bundle()\r\n     .on('end', cb)\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nthat will build all pages in one go. then you probably need a separate gulp task to extract the source maps from the generated files. it might need some tweaking, I haven't actually used factor-bundle myself.",
